-- Rand Strengthens Against Dollar, Reversing Earlier 0.8 Percent Decline
-- B y   G a r t h   T h e u n i s s e n
-- 2010-09-28T15:46:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-28/rand-strengthens-against-dollar-for-third-day-reversing-earlier-0-8-fall.html
South Africa’s rand strengthened
against the dollar for a third day in late trade, reversing
earlier losses of as much as 0.8 percent.  The rand appreciated as much as 0.4 percent to 6.9656 per
dollar, near the strongest level since January 2008. The
currency traded 0.3 percent stronger at 6.9769 as of 5:39 p.m.
in Johannesburg, from a previous close of 6.9953.  Earlier today the rand traded as weak as 7.0509 as concern
Europe’s debt crisis may worsen curbed demand for higher-
yielding, emerging market assets.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Garth Theunissen at 
 gtheunissen@bloomberg.net  